thread.text:
Thanks, everyone! I will definitely give QuickPic a try.
@benjamminh - thanks for tip, but I prefer to stick with what comes from the official store, I've had really bad luck in the past with downloads from unknown sources and stay clear of them these days, especially with a brand new phone that is (at the moment) bug free.
@sangs - you are correct in that there is an option to turn off cloud back up. The cloud wasn't really the issue I was having with Google pics, I only mentioned it in my original post to say that it wasn't something I was looking for in a recommendation. It's more the layout and the organization of Google pics I don't care for. To each their own :-)

Still setting it up this morning, currently transferring my music collection via iSyncr. 
-- Love the fact that Moto has enabled Adoptable Storage - something some other manufacturers - !COUGH! Samsung, LG - !COUGH! - have avoided doing. **** (EDIT - OK, maybe Samsung and LG knew what they were doing by disabling Adoptable Storage. As my music was populating, I kept receiving warnings that there was no more storage available. I assumed it would go away. It did not. Phone restarted on it's own, the message about having no storage available popped up again, along with one saying there wasn't enough space for messages. So Adoptable Storage will be TURNED OFF for me from here on in. That's one huge glitch!) ****
-- Installed the flexible glass screen protector from Verizon. Very easy install and now no worries about scratches;
-- Was surprised to find several "bloatware" items that were able to be completely uninstalled, instead of just disabled. The others have already been disabled and just like that - TADA! - no bloatware, not that that will stop people from ******** about it, for whatever reason;
-- Also the "Moto" lettering right about the fingerprint sensor is less noticeable than photos have made it appear. It's a very dull white. I can't even see it when I look from certain angles;
-- The "chin" is also much smaller in person;
-- Security patch is on May 1 edition. Ran a "System Update" check and none was found;
-- Screen is very bright and punchy. Side-by-side with my S7 Edge shows very little difference, if any at all;
-- Out of the box, battery was at 80 percent. "Turbo Charger" had it to 100 within 25 minutes or so;
-- One suggestion that I always do during setup. Don't sign in to ANY accounts during the setup process. Skip all that so you can delete/disable whatever you want before it auto updates. Then go to "Accounts" and add what you want.
Setup has gone smoothly, but too early to tell how much I enjoy it yet.
